  <prompt>
    Implement the **client-side low-confidence badge** on `InsightsResponseRenderer`
    (built by task 026). This is the R5 client-side resolution of Insights contract
    v1.1 decision **D5** (spec §8.2 / plan.md D2-18) — instead of accepting the
    Insights team's default (no badge), R5 surfaces a low-confidence UX hint *purely
    in the renderer*, requiring **zero Insights contract change**.

    Behavior is mechanical and small:

    1. The renderer receives a response payload that includes a `confidence` field
       (number in `[0, 1]`) on both the playbook structured envelope and the RAG
       prose envelope per integration brief v1.0 §4.
    2. When `confidence < threshold` (default `0.6`, configurable via R5 frontend
       settings), render a Fluent v9 `Badge` (preferred for compact placement
       alongside the response header) OR `MessageBar` (preferred if the renderer's
       layout calls for a banner) with the **exact** text:
       **"Low confidence — verify before relying"**.
    3. When `confidence &gt;= threshold`, the badge is absent (no DOM node rendered).
    4. The threshold MUST be configurable via R5 settings (read from app config /
       feature config — see Step 3 for the exact location to verify). Default
       `0.6` per spec FR-15 Acceptance + spec.md Assumptions §"Confidence threshold
       default".
    5. The badge MUST pass dark-mode visual check against `webDarkTheme` per
       ADR-021.

    Per R5 §3.2 (CLAUDE.md): **no new feature flag**. The threshold is a
    *configuration value*, not a kill-switch. Per R5 §3.1 reuse mandate: use the
    EXISTING Fluent v9 `Badge` (or `MessageBar`) primitives from
    `@fluentui/react-components`; do NOT build a parallel UI component. Per R5
    §3.6: this task is **pure frontend** — no BFF code change, no
    `dotnet publish` measurement, BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.

    The visual placement decision (header-adjacent `Badge` vs banner
    `MessageBar`) is delegated to the renderer's layout — Step 4 documents the
    chosen primitive in task notes for cross-reference with task 026's
    `InsightsResponseRenderer` design. Either primitive satisfies FR-15 per spec
    text "Fluent v9 `Badge` **or** `MessageBar`".
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React 19 + Fluent UI v9 component developer with experience extending an
    existing renderer with a small typed sub-component. Familiar with Spaarke's
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets` package (where `InsightsResponseRenderer` lives per task
    026), R5 frontend settings conventions (app config / feature config), Fluent
    v9 semantic-token + dark-mode discipline (ADR-021), and React 19 hooks +
    typed prop interfaces (ADR-022). Understands ADR-018 §"Flag Scope Discipline"
    — configuration value vs feature flag distinction.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `InsightsResponseRenderer` is extended with a `LowConfidenceBadge` sub-component
    (or inline JSX block — Step 4 picks the cleaner of the two) that renders a
    Fluent v9 `Badge` or `MessageBar` with the exact text **"Low confidence —
    verify before relying"** when the response payload's `confidence &lt; threshold`.
    The threshold is read from an R5 frontend settings source (a `useSettings()`
    hook, a config module, or the existing settings-loading pattern used elsewhere
    in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` — Step 3 verifies the exact location); default value
    is `0.6`. When `confidence &gt;= threshold`, NO badge DOM node is rendered (not
    a hidden node).

    Both renderer paths (`path: "playbook"` and `path: "rag"`) honor the badge
    consistently — same threshold, same text, same primitive choice.

    Dark mode passes for both render states (badge visible / badge absent). The
    component is typed (no `any` in public exports). Unit tests cover threshold
    boundary (just below / at / just above), threshold reconfiguration, both
    response paths, and absent / null confidence handling.

    Per FR-15 / SC-14: badge appears for `confidence &lt; threshold`; absent for
    `confidence &gt;= threshold`; threshold configurable; both verified by tests
    and by smoke-test screenshots. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.

    The `code-review` + `adr-check` FULL-rigor quality gates at Step 9.5 pass.
  </goal>

