  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15">Render Fluent v9 `Badge` OR `MessageBar` with exact text "Low confidence — verify before relying" when `confidence &lt; threshold`. Threshold configurable; default 0.6. Badge appears for confidence below threshold; absent for confidence at or above threshold.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec SC-14">Verified by: hit low-confidence response → badge visible; hit high-confidence response → badge absent. Confirmed by unit tests + smoke-test screenshots.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md Assumptions">Default threshold = 0.6. Configurable via R5 settings if operator preference shifts. Affects FR-15.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST use the EXISTING Fluent v9 `Badge` or `MessageBar` primitives from `@fluentui/react-components`. MUST NOT build a parallel UI component. Cite the chosen primitive in code comments + task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 / ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline">NO new feature flag. The threshold is a *configuration value* (numeric), not a kill-switch. Threshold lives in R5 frontend settings alongside other configurable values. Verified by reviewer inspection (no `Feature:...` or `Enabled` flag added).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 / ADR-029">BFF publish-size — N/A; this task adds frontend code only. Confirm publish-size delta = 0 MB in task notes. NO `dotnet publish` run required.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens ONLY — no hex/rgba/Fluent v8 imports. Dark mode MUST be tested and pass; badge MUST be legible against both `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`. Use semantic intent (`appearance="filled"` / `color="warning"` for `Badge`, or `intent="warning"` for `MessageBar`) consistent with low-confidence semantics.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only — functional component (or inline JSX), typed props, no `any` in exports. Hooks-only state management.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` shared library adjacent to (or inside) `InsightsResponseRenderer`. Context-agnostic — no `Xrm` references, no PCF-specific imports, no SpaarkeAi-shell-specific imports.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — N/A for frontend component. Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 §3.5 Zone B boundary">R5 is a Zone B consumer of the Insights contract. This task does NOT modify any Insights-internal type; it consumes the `confidence` field from the renderer's already-parsed response payload (produced upstream by task 024's `InsightsQueryToolHandler` + task 026's renderer). NO new BFF code, NO new HTTP call, NO Insights-internal type referenced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus is closed at 4 channels — N/A for this task (no new event types). Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.0 §4 (response schema)">`confidence` field is a `number` in `[0, 1]` on both `path: "playbook"` and `path: "rag"` envelopes per integration brief. Tool MUST handle absent / null / out-of-range values gracefully (treat as "no confidence signal" → no badge rendered, defensive default).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Exact badge text MUST be "Low confidence — verify before relying" (en-dash; case-sensitive; no trailing punctuation). The text is FR-15 and SC-14 prose; deviations are spec violations.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">When `confidence &gt;= threshold`, NO badge DOM node is rendered (not a hidden node with `display: none`). Verified by unit test asserting `queryByText("Low confidence — verify before relying") === null`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Threshold reconfiguration MUST be reactive — if R5 settings change at runtime (e.g., operator updates feature config), subsequent renders honor the new threshold. Most likely no-op given component re-renders on prop / context change; verify in test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F test obligation">N/A for the BFF test obligation (this is frontend-only). Frontend tests required: at minimum the 5 unit tests in Step 6.</constraint>
  </constraints>

