    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 `Badge` for compact inline status" location="@fluentui/react-components (Badge)">
        Compact inline status pill — preferred for header-adjacent placement next
        to response title or correlation-id. Use `appearance="filled"` and
        `color="warning"` (Fluent v9 semantic color slot — maps to amber tones in
        light, muted amber in dark per semantic-token discipline). Renders ~20px
        tall; suitable for response-header rows. Example shape:
        `&lt;Badge appearance="filled" color="warning"&gt;Low confidence — verify before relying&lt;/Badge&gt;`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 `MessageBar` for banner-style status" location="@fluentui/react-components (MessageBar)">
        Full-width banner — preferred when the renderer's layout calls for a
        visually prominent advisory above the response body. Use `intent="warning"`
        for semantic styling. Renders as a single horizontal row with icon + body
        text. Example shape:
        `&lt;MessageBar intent="warning"&gt;&lt;MessageBarBody&gt;Low confidence — verify before relying&lt;/MessageBarBody&gt;&lt;/MessageBar&gt;`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Configurable threshold via R5 settings" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/ (R5 settings convention — verify at Step 3)">
        R5 frontend settings convention is the existing config-loading pattern in
        `@spaarke/ai-widgets` or the SpaarkeAi shell. Likely candidates: a
        `useSettings()` / `useConfig()` hook, a `widgetConfig` module, or a
        context provider. Step 3 verifies the exact location. Read the threshold
        as `settings.insights?.confidenceThreshold ?? 0.6`. Default is hard-coded
        in the renderer alongside the read so it works even if settings are not
        provided.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Conditional rendering — no DOM node when absent" location="N/A — React 19 idiom">
        Use a conditional expression returning `null` rather than a hidden element:
        `{confidence != null &amp;&amp; confidence &lt; threshold ? &lt;Badge ...&gt;...&lt;/Badge&gt; : null}`.
        Verified by `queryByText` returning `null` in absent case (NOT a
        `getByText` with `style.display === 'none'` check, which would still find
        the node).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Defensive handling of confidence field" location="N/A — input-validation idiom">
        The `confidence` field may be: a number in [0, 1] (normal); `null` (some
        Insights paths may omit); `undefined` (response shape variation); out of
        range (defensive — treat as "no signal"). Render the badge ONLY when
        `confidence` is a finite number in [0, 1] AND `confidence &lt; threshold`.
        All other cases → no badge. Document this in code comments.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships the Insights tool integration (`insights.query`) through the
      SpaarkeAi three-pane shell. Task 026 (D2-16) builds `InsightsResponseRenderer`
      — a React component that renders both Insights response paths (playbook
      structured envelope + RAG citation-grounded prose). This task (028) extends
      that renderer with a small client-side advisory: when the response's
      `confidence` is below a configurable threshold (default 0.6), surface a
      "Low confidence — verify before relying" badge.

      Per spec §8.2 D5 + spec.md Open Decisions row "Insights v1.1 D5
      (confidence floor)": R5 explicitly chose to implement this *client-side*
      instead of asking the Insights team to add a server-side badge. This is
      "pure R5 work; no contract change" — preserves the v1.0 / v1.1 contract
      surface and isolates UX policy from the Insights server.

      The 0.6 threshold default comes from spec.md Assumptions §"Confidence
      threshold default" and is configurable via R5 settings to allow operator
      tuning post-launch without code change. Per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline
      and R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2: this is a *configuration value* (numeric), not a
      feature flag. The badge is unconditional UX surface area; only the
      threshold is tunable.

      This task is the LAST of P2-G6 (Insights tool integration suite — 024 tool
      handler, 025 subject resolution, 026 renderer, 027 clickable citations,
      028 confidence badge). It is small (~2h estimated), parallel-safe with
      siblings 024/025/027, and depends only on 026 because the badge is a
      sub-component of (or inline JSX block within) `InsightsResponseRenderer`.

      The renderer is in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` per ADR-012 + R5 CLAUDE.md §8
      ("Frontend `InsightsResponseRenderer` component (NEW)"). Exact file path
      verified at Step 1 against task 026's outputs.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="026" status="required-blocking">
        D2-16 — `InsightsResponseRenderer` two-path React component. This task
        EXTENDS that renderer with the low-confidence badge. Task 026 MUST be ✅
        before task 028 implementation; if 026 is 🔲 or 🔄, STOP and report.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 024 (D2-14) — `InsightsQueryToolHandler` produces the response
