  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`InsightsResponseRenderer` renders a Fluent v9 `Badge` (with `color="warning"`) OR `MessageBar` (with `intent="warning"`) containing the EXACT text "Low confidence — verify before relying" (en-dash U+2014; no trailing punctuation) when the response payload's `confidence` field is a finite number in [0, 1] and `confidence &lt; threshold`. Confirmed by unit Test 1 (below threshold) covering both `path: "playbook"` and `path: "rag"` response shapes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">When `confidence &gt;= threshold`, NO badge DOM node is rendered (returns `null`, not a hidden node). Confirmed by unit Test 2 (at threshold) + Test 3 (above threshold) asserting `queryByText("Low confidence — verify before relying") === null`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Threshold default = 0.6 per spec FR-15 + spec.md Assumptions. Confirmed by unit Test 1 (confidence 0.5 with no explicit threshold prop → badge visible).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Threshold is configurable via R5 settings. The exact settings location is documented in task notes (either an existing convention extended OR a new minimal config module at a documented path). Reactive reconfiguration honored — re-rendering with a new threshold immediately updates badge visibility. Confirmed by unit Test 4.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Defensive handling — when `confidence` is `null`, `undefined`, `NaN`, out of [0, 1] range, or not a number, NO badge is rendered. Confirmed by unit Test 5 (parametrized over edge values).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NO new feature flag introduced (per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 + ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline). Threshold is a configuration value (numeric), not a kill-switch. Confirmed by diff inspection / grep — no `Feature:...:Enabled` boolean added.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark mode passes — badge renders legibly against `webDarkTheme` using only Fluent v9 semantic tokens (no hex / rgba / Fluent v8 imports). Evidence captured in task notes (screenshot reference or harness output path).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Smoke test against the SpaarkeAi shell with low-confidence + high-confidence + boundary (= threshold) responses confirms behavior end-to-end on both response paths (playbook + RAG). Confirmed by smoke-test screenshots / DevTools traces in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No BFF code changed by this task — pure frontend. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB. Confirmed in task notes (no `dotnet publish` run required; `git diff src/server/` shows no changes).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zone B boundary preserved — no Insights-internal type referenced; consumes the already-parsed response payload only. Confirmed by reviewer inspection at Step 9.5 + `adr-check` (ADR-013 §3.5) pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build passes: `npm run build` in `Spaarke.AI.Widgets` succeeds with no TypeScript errors and no new lint warnings. Tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass at Step 9.5 (ADR-021, ADR-022, ADR-018, ADR-012, ADR-013 §3.5 confirmed; ADR-010, ADR-029, ADR-030 N/A confirmed).</criterion>
